      "content": "While the immediate prevention of a massacre is a point often raised, focusing solely on that narrow outcome ignores the long-term strategic disaster. The intervention was a flawed application of \"humanitarian intervention\" doctrine, which inevitably leads to state collapse when the underlying political structures are not addressed. The failure to build a viable post-Gaddafi state proves that the action was strategically unsound, regardless of the initial humanitarian impulse.",
      "source": "target",
