    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear you on the long-term stuff, but it feels like you're almost dismissing the humanitarian aspect entirely. if a policy prevents a genocide in the short term, does that not hold some inherent value, even if the aftermath is messy? or are you saying that strategic stability should always trump human lives in these scenarios?",
